The paper deals with the distributed computation of the maximum coverage problem, which involves partitioning a collection of sets across multiple machines and finding a subset of k sets that cover the most number of elements. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper's focus on communication cost and round complexity suggests that cs.DC and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS and cs.GT, with cs.DM also a possibility given the problem's relevance to data mining.
